#ROOMS
#5000
Forest Preserve Trailhead~
A cedar sign marks the entrance to the @@GWhispering Forest Preserve@@N, its carved letters worn smooth by seasons of weather. Packed earth trails branch north and east into the shade of ancient pines and cedar beyond the sign post. Hikers have worn smooth grooves in the soil where countless boots have passed over the years. The air smells of cedar resin and damp earth, cool even in warm afternoons. Directional markers are bolted to a post beside the sign, pointing deeper into the preserve.

